Note:
Go Emitter - Buffered output for Go code generation

All buffer management, character/string emission, and indentation logic
is delegated to the shared byte-buffer foundation in emitter_common.runa.

Conventions:
- Tab indentation per gofmt convention
- Null-terminated output strings
:End Note

Import "../emitter_common.runa" as EmitterCommon

@Reasoning:
Typed view of the shared raw 24-byte emitter header for Go-backend
call sites. Storage management is delegated to emitter_common.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Three Integer fields (buffer/capacity/length) at offsets 0/8/16.
@End Implementation

Type called "GoEmitter":
    buffer as Integer
    capacity as Integer
    length as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Named Go emitter constructor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_create.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_go_emitter" returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_create from EmitterCommon
End Process

@Reasoning:
Paired destructor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_destroy.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
Caller must drop the pointer after this call.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "destroy_go_emitter" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_destroy from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Reserve capacity ahead of a large emit.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_ensure_capacity.
@End Implementation

Process called "ensure_capacity" takes emitter as Integer, needed as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_ensure_capacity from EmitterCommon with emitter, needed
End Process

@Reasoning:
Append a single byte. Hot helper for Go punctuation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_emit_byte.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_char" takes emitter as Integer, char as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, char
End Process

@Reasoning:
Append a null-terminated string for Go keywords and identifiers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_emit_string.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_string" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit text then LF; common at the end of a Go statement.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the string then LF.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_line" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Named newline emitter.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits LF (byte 10).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_newline" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single space helper for token separation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits SP (byte 32).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_space" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single horizontal tab. gofmt uses tabs (not spaces) for indentation,
so this is the dominant whitespace primitive for Go output.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits HT (byte 9).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_tab" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 9
End Process

@Reasoning:
gofmt convention is one tab per indent level (rather than spaces).
Centralised here so the indent unit stays consistent across the Go
backend.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Loops level times emitting a tab byte (9).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_indent" takes emitter as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Tab indentation per gofmt convention - one tab per level.
    Let count be 0
    While count is less than level:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 9
        Set count to count plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Snapshot the buffer into a heap-allocated null-terminated copy.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_get_output.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_output" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Expose the current write position.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_length.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_length" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_length from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Reuse buffer for next translation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_reset.
@End Implementation

Process called "reset" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_reset from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process
